---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="Terms of Service - JSON Utility Kit"
    description="Review the terms of service governing the utilization of JSON Utility Kit. Standard as-is usage with zero warranty."
>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-8 dark:border-gray-800 mb-8">
            <h1
                class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white sm:text-4xl"
            >
                Terms of Service
            </h1>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
                Last updated: June 12, 2026
            </p>
        </div>

        <div
            class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-6 leading-relaxed"
        >
            <p>
                By accessing or using the web utility tools hosted at <strong
                    >JSON Utility Kit</strong
                >, you agree to be bound by these simple Terms of Service. If
                you do not accept these parameters, please discontinue your
                access immediately.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4"
            >
                1. As-Is Provision
            </h2>
            <p>
                All of our tools, code formats, checkers, minifiers, and
                articles are provided on an <strong>"as-is"</strong> and <strong
                    >"as-available"</strong
                > baseline without warranties of any variety, express or implied.
            </p>
            <p>
                While we make every professional attempt to validate our parsing
                scripts (like CSV flattener standardizations and tree viewers),
                we do not represent that the tool results will be completely
                error-free or suited for critical production pipelines without
                manual checking.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4"
            >
                2. Security Responsibility
            </h2>
            <p>
                Although our tools process your properties <strong
                    >strictly inside your local browser memory space</strong
                > (making it far safer than standard remote servers), we recommend
                that users do not paste highly classified government databases, system
                encryption passphrases, or trade secrets if they do not trust their
                own local computer sandbox or immediate client settings.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4"
            >
                3. Limitation of Liability
            </h2>
            <p>
                Under no circumstances shall JSON Utility Kit or its creators be
                liable for any special, direct, indirect, consequential, or
                accidental data loss, damage, loss of business revenue, or
                computer crashes resulting from using or converting documents on
                this website.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4"
            >
                4. Terms Modifications
            </h2>
            <p>
                We reserve the right to modify these guidelines at any point
                without prior notice. Continued use of this website after
                changes represent active confirmation of the newly updated
                Terms.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
